AudioPlayer.schedule: only the FIRST buffer of a session is anchored to the host-time-derived play time; subsequent buffers schedule back-to-back via player.scheduleBuffer(buffer) with no per-buffer timing math. Cross-device sync still happens via the shared start anchor + identical packet cadence on both sides. Per-packet hostTime scheduling was hyper-sensitive to sub-ms timing wobble (TimeSync EWMA shifts, dispatch queue jitter, AVAudioEngine internal clock vs mach_absolute_time discrepancy) and was the cause of the periodic gaps the user reported even after removing the 1Hz stats timers and bumping latency to 80ms. New `primed` field on AudioPlayer, reset in stop().